Sentencas: An integrated experimental/modeling approach was utilized to assess the structural integrity of Ni-yttriastabilized zirconia (YSZ) porous anode supports during the solid oxide fuel cell (SOFC) operation on coal gas containing trace amounts of phosphorus impurities.
Titulo: Effect of nickel-phosphorus interactions on structural integrity of anode-supported solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Phosphorus was chosen as a typical impurity exhibiting strong interactions with the nickel followed by second phase formation.
Titulo: Effect of nickel-phosphorus interactions on structural integrity of anode-supported solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Tests were performed using Ni-YSZ anode-supported button cells exposed to 0.5-10 ppm of phosphine in synthetic coal gas at 700-800 degrees C.
Titulo: Effect of nickel-phosphorus interactions on structural integrity of anode-supported solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The extent of Ni-P interactions was determined by a post-test scanning electron microscopy (SEM) analysis.
Titulo: Effect of nickel-phosphorus interactions on structural integrity of anode-supported solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Severe damage to the anode support due to nickel phosphide phase formation and extensive crystal coalescence was revealed, resulting in electric percolation loss.
Titulo: Effect of nickel-phosphorus interactions on structural integrity of anode-supported solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The subsequent finite element stress analyses were conducted using the actual anode support microstructures to assist in degradation mechanism explanation.
Titulo: Effect of nickel-phosphorus interactions on structural integrity of anode-supported solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Volume expansion induced by the Ni phase alteration was found to produce high stress levels such that local failure of the Ni-YSZ anode became possible under the operating conditions.
Titulo: Effect of nickel-phosphorus interactions on structural integrity of anode-supported solid oxide fuel cells
